The decomposing bodies of the men accused of killing 148 innocent people at a university were paraded in front of a crowd at a primary school .
The authorities drove the naked , bloated corpses of the four alleged terrorists around the town in a pickup truck from the mortuary to Garissa Primary School .
It comes as survivor Cynthia Cheroitich , 19 , spent two days hiding in a wardrobe and drinking body lotion to survive , was rescued after al-Shabaab gunmen stormed Garissa University College